You must embrace the basic laws of software. You must develop a mindset that every developer should have. This mindset will help you make better decisions in your daily programming journey. You can keep your program as simple as possible.
Here are the key points that every developer must master.
1. Conceiving The Purpose of Software :the purpose of the software is not to show off how intelligent you are.
2.The Goals of Software Design: Your design should be easy for you and helpful for others.
3. (Mis)understanding:nderstanding is the key difference between a bad developer and a good developer. 
4. Simplicity: "Stupid, dumb simple"
5. Complexity :Your main purpose is to control complexity, not to create it.
6. Maintenance: All changes require maintenance.
7. Consistency
8. Prioritizing
9. Solving Problems:Think before acting.
10. Good enough is fine:Perfect is the enemy of good.
11. Predictions
12. Assumptions
13. Stop Reinventing
14. Resistance
15. Automation
16. Code measurement
17. Productivity
18. Testing
19. (Under)Estimation :Everything takes longer than you think.
20. Running Away From Rewriting
21. Documentation and Commenting
22. Picking Technologies (Tools, Libraries, etc.)
23. Self-Development
24. Don’t be a hero
25. Don’t Ask Questions… Ask For Help..
